content.div:
Many young Canadians move into their own place at 18. In Justin Bieber's case, he's moving into a $10.8 million Hollywood mansion. But hey, the kid reportedly has a roommate: girlfriend Selena Gomez.

--

The first promo for Oprah's interview with Whitney Houston's daughter, brother and sister-in-law has landed. Expect plenty of tears, hugs -- and questions about Bobby Brown.

--

Shocker: Kim Kardashian did something tacky. She apparently kept her wedding presents. Kris Humphries and Miss Manners don't approve.

--

New details on the Canadian premiere of the Hunger Games have surfaced. Stars Liam Hemsworth (Gale), Josh Hutcherson (Peeta) and Vancouver-based actor Alexander Ludwig (he plays tribute Cato) will attend the Toronto red-carpet premiere Monday, March 19. (Ludwig will also appear in Vancouver March 21.) Fans are expected to fight each other to the death on premiere day, all in the hopes of laying eyes on a District 12 dreamboat.

--

The lyrics on Madonna's M.D.N.A. will reveal more than the correct spelling of "Luv," it seems. A leaked snippet of album track "I Don't Give A" seems to trash the pop queen's ex-husband Guy Ritchie. (Sample lyric: "I tried to be a good girl/ I tried to be your wife/ Diminished myself/ And I swallowed my light.")

--

Tim Tebow was asked to star on The Bachelor. For those who desperately want to see this happen, never underestimate the power of prayer. And ratings.

--

McG will direct a found-footage horror movie about a Ouija board. Please note it will be completely different from every other horror movie to involve a ouija board, because this one comes to you from the fine people at Hasbro. (Expect a scene where a mysterious voice from beyond the grave pimps out Transformers 4, coming soon to a theatre near you.)

--

This is what a country song by Real Housewife Kim Zolciak sounds like.

--

Vanessa Hudgens went blonde for a movie. Let's all spaz about it.

--

In other follicle-related headlines, Pink's hair is pink again. She's apparently gone back to her signature hue to tell fans a new album is on the way.

--

This is a real thing that is really happening: the Barenaked Ladies are writing music for an Animal House musical.

--

Check back to Dose.ca throughout the day for your entertainment fix.
